reviews: Absolutely amazing hotel. It was comfortable and pretty and located nicely in town. The concierge was incredibly helpful with booking other tours and visits in town as well. Highly recommend this space!

Great location close to 2 Metro-stations, but you can also easily walk to several attractions.
Super-friendly and helpful staff from check-in, breakfast till check-out.
Nice rooms, good size, clean, different interior designs.
Modern cinema-themed hotel-design, but you can still see the historical origins. Good breakfast. Coffee and sweet snacks all day. Gym in the basement.

Perfect stay!! Thank you.

We had a nice stay at Hotel le 123 Sebastopol, beds were comfortable, shower was decent, location was within reasonable walk or a quick metro ride to everywhere we wanted to go and the front desk staff was really helpful and kind and spoke many languages. They helpfully arranged a transfer to Gare Montparnasse for us as well.

The minibar setup is a nice refresher when you come in from a long day. Would definitely stay again!

Exceptional service. So accommodating and friendly. Rooms were cozy and beds comfy with a nice size bathroom. We will be back for sure!! Loved the outdoor patio space and the complimentary beverages available in the lobby.

Beautiful modern hotel with an adorable cinema theme. The service was excellent from every member of the staff. Clean rooms, small but not too small. Perfect location to explore all the city has to offer. Highly recommend!

Absolutely wonderful hotel! Excellent staff and very comfortable room. Breakfast was delicious and perfect location. Would absolutely stay here again. The hotel was also very secure with main door locked after a certain hour.

This is a small hotel about a mile from the Louve and other attractions along the Seine. Walking is a good way to get around. It's close to the Paris Metro ( beware of pickpockets) and the surface bus goes right by the door. There's a nice little park across the street if you like to sit outside and take in the Paris life. There are numerous sidewalk bistros within a couple blocks. Lots of great food without having to go to an expensive restaurant, and it really captures the feel of the city.

The staff is very friendly and English speaking. One staff member we spoke to was fluent in six languages. There is a nice coffee and snack bar that is open through the evening with lots of luscious goodies. If you book directly with the hotel you get free hot breakfast buffet. It is clean and comfortable. Rooms are a little small by US standards, but about right for Europe. The theme of the hotel is movies, so you see some movie theme in the decor.

Beds are comfortable. The bedding has thick comforters to keep you warm. My only suggestion to the management is it can get too warm. A choice of regular sheets and blankets would be helpful.

The room has a TV, but of course the programming is all in French. If you want English or another language, bring a laptop or pad computer, and subscribe to a couple streaming channels. You can cast directly to the TV with whatever programming you can get off hotel's the wi-fi. The wi-fi password is obtained from the TV.

This is my second visit to Paris, and I stayed at this hotel both times. I recommend it.

This is a fabulous boutique hotel located in an ideal location to explore Paris. For a walker, everything is within 45 minutes; metro, which is just down the street, much faster. The room was on the smaller side, but large bathroom, comfortable bed and fluffy towels. Mini bar with non-alcoholic beverages is free and restocked daily. The comfortable lobby/eating area always has beverages, fruits, pastries, and snacks available. I’d definitely add breakfast to the room; it was very good. Workout room was limited, but all that is needed. We loved the decor and all the French film references.

We loved our stay here! Beautiful hotel and friendly staff. The breakfast was excellent as was the complimentary pastry/dessert spread that was out from 2pm-2am daily. Great location away from the main tourist area but still walking distance, and also close to two metro stations. Could not have been happier with this spot!

We were on our honeymoon to Paris and stayed at this hotel, which turned out to be an excellent decision! Room was bright, modern and comfortable. Our experience was full of nice touches! Staff was very welcoming and helpful. They greeted us every time we left/entered the hotel, and also gifted us a bottle of champagne and a box of macarons to celebrate our honeymoon. Complimentary in-room mini bar with a good variety of non-alcoholic drinks was replenished daily.

Location was perfect! Felt very comfortable walking the clean streets. Commuting with the nearest metro line M4 was also very pleasant - trains felt cleaner and more updated.

Highly recommended for first time visitors to Paris!

Great hotel! Clean, friendly, well located to subway that can get to major sites. Walking distance to le marais. Small rooms but clean and perfect if you don’t spend a lot of time at the hotel. Thank you for a great stay.

The hotel was super terrific with the movie set theme, the rooms were most gorgues and had a great view from our windows.

The staff were superfriendly and catered to our needs. Shoutout to the Filipino staffs who made our stay feel like we were back home and for having a rice at the breakfast buffet was awesome for my family.

Overall 5 stars and would like to return to this hotel in the near future.

C’est tres tres bien accommodation. I went with my husband and mother-in-law to Paris and we stayed here in Le 123 Sebastopol-Astotel; we had a splendid time here and the front desk and kitchen personnel are very friendly and accommodating. This hotel is highly recommended when staying in Paris!

This was a wonderful place to stay in Paris. The best part about the Hotel is the friendly and welcoming staff. Guests are made to feel very special and the location is outstanding, close to the Marais, lots of excellent dining choices and the Metro station is across the road. My room was stylishly decorated in a black and white theme. I was slow on the uptake of their excellent afternoon tea for guests but once I tried it, I really looked forward to the coffee and sweet treats after a day of sightseeing. Thank you for a terrific stay, I hope I will return one day.

The location is excellent, with a Metro station 2 minutes walk away and many bistros & shops nearby. The hotel is delightfully decorated and offered some really lovely extras: free minibar in the room, restocked daily (non-alcoholic drinks) and complimentary afternoon tea/snacks and drinks available downstairs from 2:00pm till late. There is also a movie theatre showing free movies. The staff were welcoming and helpful and the room was larger than expected. Would definitely stay again.

Excellent location. Staff were extremely friendly and super helpful
Very comfortable beds..pristine clean rooms and bathroom.
Lovely breakfast and free coffee cake and fruit ongoing in lobby from 14:00 to late night
Altogether a week's great stay in Paris

The staff is friendly, efficient, and comfortable in multiple languages. The premises are spotless and modern. Their movie theme is attractive.

There's a Metro station right across the street (although you must have a ticket to enter that particular station.)

A full breakfast buffet, including 7 hot dishes, a variety of cheese, pastries, charcuterie, salads, fruit and smoked salmon is available, and a good value at €15. They had no problem having gluten-free bread available for my wife, provided we let them know the night before.

Complimentary snacks and beverages (non-alcoholic) are available during the day, and they even fill the mini-bar in each room (again, non-alcoholic beverages only) each day.

Exceptional staff - kind and helpful. They cleaned the rooms every day. The room had a small sweet terrace, the food was delicious. I recommend with both hands. Very good location, close to metro, supermarket, cafes, everything you need is 2 min walk. Price = quality! The Louvre is 20 minutes walking distance. Next time we visit Paris, we will stay there again.

I had a wonderful experience. The hotel is located in a very convenient location, which made it easy for me to explore the city. The ambiance of the hotel was very interesting and unique, and it really added to the overall experience.

One of the things that really stood out to me about the hotel was the warm welcome that I received when I walked in. The staff was always friendly and welcoming, which made me feel right at home. Additionally, the hotel offers a great afternoon tea time, where they provide all kinds of drinks, sweets, and fruits for guests to enjoy.

The room decor was also very lively and clean, and it really added to the overall experience. The hotel provided beverages, which was a nice touch. Overall, I highly recommend the Hôtel Le 123 Sébastopol - Astotel and I will definitely be coming back in the future.

Especially Mr. ADIL always gave us warm greeting.

Absolutely loved our stay at this quirky, wonderful hotel. From the second we stepped in the front door to the moment we left four days later the staff were super friendly and helpful - and nothing was too much trouble. Breakfast was fabulous and the complimentary drinks and snacks very welcome. Our room, whilst not huge, had everything we needed with comfortable beds and some really funky touches. The hotel is in a great location with a good selection of restaurants right on the doorstep and a Metro station just a minute away. The icing on the cake is the lovely cinema, which can be booked out (for free) to watch the film of your choice...our 12-year-old son LOVED it (as did we). Can't recommend highly enough.

Lovely hotel in beautiful 3rd Arr. staff very helpful, room was beautiful with a great view of park across street. Although hotel does not have formal restaurant or bar, they do offer a great breakfast.

Excellent service- very responsive staff;, great room and amenities; convenient location - walking distance from nice neighborhoods and well served by metro/ bus line. Adil at the front desk is a gem!

Everyone was friendly and the place is actually walking distance to everything we wanted to do. Everyone is so friendly and breakfast was nice. I would choose to stay here again in the future. Thank you.

A lovely, cosy hotel in Paris. Great location - very close to major tourist spots, like Louvre, Norte Dame de Paris or Centre Pompidou. Only a couple of metro stations away from Gare du Nord. Every floor is styled under an iconic cinematic legend - we lived on Ennio Morricone's floor. Fantastic breakfasts - we had all we needed—many good restaurants in the area. A complimentary snack/drink buffet is available in the lobby during the day. The hotel's main highlight is the cinema - you can rent it just for yourself; a great collection of movies; my mum and I finally watched The Good, the Bad and the Ugly - it seemed appropriate since Morricone wrote the music for the film. Hope to revisit this incredible place! The hotel is definitely worth it!

Cute common areas with a very friendly staff who spoke multiple languages. My son played their grand piano while we enjoyed some evening pastries. Our family room had 2 bedrooms, one with a king bed and the other with two twins and a rollaway bed to accommodate 5. The room was spacious with two bathrooms and a complimentary mini bar of soft drinks. An adorable space with great decor. The hotel is right across from the Metro and is walking distance to several restaurants and bakeries. Highly recommended with no complaints and will definitely stay again!

The staff at this hotel are wonderful — very friendly and helpful, from checkin to checkout.

I stayed three nights and found the value and location to be great. Proximity to two metro stations and many cafes was great.

The hotel has a movie theme, which I found a little kitschy — but my room was well appointed, very clean, and I appreciated the complimentary beverage minibar. I also enjoyed the afternoon tea — sweet treats and a nice selection of nonalcoholic beverages and coffee in the lobby each afternoon.

I’d definitely consider staying here again!

The staff was very welcoming and helpful especially the front desk staff. Rooms were clean. Breakfast and afternoon snacks were good (especially the doughnuts). Overall it was a good experience during our first time in Paris.

Wonderful stay for our Spring Break 2023. Enjoyed daily breakfast and friendly staff. Room was made daily and stocked appropriately. Interned was good since my son was able to complete his schoolwork daily.

The hotel was amazing. Great location. The staff was very helpful for all of our questions and provided guidance. The rooms were comfortable and breakfast was great. We are a family of 4 and the connecting room was the perfect size.

The hotel was excellent. The receptionists were really kind and polite. I booked the room with only 2 days in advance, and for some reason (I don't know) it was very economical, and it included also breakfast. The hotel is well located, and the room and the breakfast was great. So nothing to complain about.

We stayed in this hotel for our short City break to Paris in March 2023. The staff were all very warm and friendly and the hotel was quirky and clean. It was located within easy walking distance from Louvre and many other tourist attractions including many restaurants and bars. The hotel has a good breakfast selection. We would recommend this hotel and would be happy to stay again.

This was a nice hotel with very pleasant and helpful staff. I would probably give just over 4 stars if I could. Our room was a good size but not very practical. There was little hanging room even for only 3 nights stay and particularly with winter coats etc. There wasn’t much storage generally and even the bed side tables were boxes which didn’t open. The bathroom was quite smart and it was good to have a proper bath tub but again no hooks for wet towels.The free mini bar ( soft drinks) was a nice touch and the provision of robes and slippers was great as we only brought cabin luggage.
Breakfast was average. We needed to ask for coffee from the machine which was very good rather than fromthe pot which was offered which was not.
The afternoon tea available from 2 pm was excellent- really nice flans and madeleines etc. This was very welcome after a busy day out. We didn’t book the cinema but this sounded fun as well.
The staff allowed us to leave our luggage on the day of departure and also to have the snacks even though check out was at 12pm.
The location was good and the metro - Reamour- Sebastopol was 3 minutes down the road. We might well stay again despite a few gripes.

Wow!! What an absolutely gorgeous hotel with amazing service. So grateful to the front desk staff for starting our stay in Paris on such a beautiful note! The afternoon tea (included) is such a lovely touch as well. We will definitely come back here !!!!

Awesome hotel, really well located, but still quiet and peaceful. It seems new (or newly renovated at least) and it is well decorated. Breakfast had a great variety and all-day afternoon tea was amazing addition! I found the staff to be very friendly and helpful, and not only the reception team, restaurant/service staff too!
Excellent stay in all aspects, well done.

Stayed with my daughter for our first weekend in Paris. Great little but perfectly formed hotel in a great location just 10 minutes from Gare du Nord and equally well placed for all the sights due to the metro being a short 4 minute stroll away. Lovely clean room with mini bar free and restocked daily. We had room 212 with 2 small balconies overlooking the street and square opposite. Lovely seats to sit and watch Paris go by but very cold while we were there! Staff were exceptional from start to finish, friendly, welcoming, helpful and hospitable. Would definitely stay again if ever back in Paris.

My friend and I went to Paris for a shopping trip for 3 days back in January 23. Both of us were so pleased with our choice to stay in this cute, niche, calm and friendly hotel. There are spacious cinema, gym, lovely breakfast, all-day coffee/tea/cakes. Very comfortable large bed, warm, quiet and clean! Great locations to tour Paris without logistic transporting difficulties! On top of that, the great receptionist - Anjanette was superb! Giving all the helps she can to order taxi, guide for food & shopping etc!

Great hotel, rooms are big, it is in a great location as you are walking distance to major sites, and also close to 4 metro lines. Breakfast is yummy and a lot to pick from. Staff are very friendly, customer focused, and make you feel at home. They have a great theatre where you can rent movies. I will stay here again and highly recommend it.

Great staying at beautiful hotel with excellent staff. Breakfast is excellent. The staff is very friendly and always available for you. The director listened to our request and immediately implemented a solution. I also totally recommend it for the team-time concept: you can visit any Astotel in Paris between 2pm and 2am and get free coffee/tea and cakes.

Excellent hotel as our base for a weekend in Paris. The facilities in the hotel were good and the service from the staff was excellent. Great location for the Metro & good bars, supermarkets and restaurants nearby. Couldn't fault it at all

A lovely hotel in a great location. The rooms were very modern, comfortable and clean.

But without doubt, the best part of the hotel is the staff! The room attendants, breakfast staff, porters, receptionists are all so friendly and professional (especially Adil!). They really made my stay and I will for sure be back as a result.

A funky cinema themed hotel. Room was bright, clean and quiet. Hotel situated in a new location fir us which we found to be an excellent opportunity to explore a less touristy area. Staff were charming, breakfast was plentiful with lots of options.

The staff , hotel everything about the experience was fantastic. The rooms are so clean , and beautifully decorated . The breakfast has everything you could wish for . This will be my hotel in Paris from now on . Amazing . Thank you :-)

We were pleasantly surprised by the generous welcome in this hotel. Everybody was really friendly and ready to help. And everything, but really everything, is linked to the theme of “movies & filmstars”. Breakfast was really good, also the afternoon snacks. A movie theatre and fitness room on top. A great experience!

Super happy with my stay. Clean elegant nice vibes nice decoration nice breakfast. And in a beautiful neighborhood. + the price wasnt bad either. Recomended 👍👍

Writting this to fill the word count what a stupid system

This is a brilliant hotel! From the moment we walked through the door we felt welcomed and looked after. AJ on the front desk was an absolute delight to deal with, as were the rest of the time. We were there for a girls weekend away, with my friend and our daughters who are both 14, to celebrate our children's birthdays. They both received a little gift as we arrived. One of our rooms was upgraded, though both rooms were lovely, and we were made to feel like special guests.

This hotel has some excellent features that sets it aside from the rest. Firstly, the generous and clever offer of pastries and non-alcoholic drinks from 2pm until 2am, beautifully laid out. And you can go to any hotel in their group to enjoy this benefit! A great relief after a day of walking in Paris, plus a money saver as we didn't buy as many pastries when we were out!

Secondly, they have a cinema room downstairs that you can book and use for free. Our teenagers loved it! We watched a movie together in our PJS the first night after dinner, and the girls went back on their own on the second night and watched another movie. Such a wonderful treat and beautifully presented and looked after.

The hotel is movie themed which feels so fun and fresh. All in all, great service, great facilities, great features ... oh and a great breakfast. We'll be staying here again when we next visit Paris and I recommend you do the same!

A truly boutique hotel and an absolute find! Incredibly well-located and amazing interiors. They provide free afternoon snacks which can also be enjoyed in 16 other hotels of Astotel group, which is a lovely touch! What I appreciate the most are their amazing staffs especially the reception team, Anjanette, Xiaolan, Mourad and Adyl! They made my stay in Paris so special! Would come back in a heartbeat!

Excellent stay in the centre of Paris! The rooms were very clean, and the staff always ready to assist us. The metro station is in short distance from the hotel. We would gladly come back to this hotel.

I highly recommend the hotel. From
The moment I arrived the staff was wonderful and made me feel so comfortable. Xiaolan was so friendly and accommodating so I really appreciate her great customer service.
Great location to subways and walking. Breakfast was very good and again - all
Of the staff was great and very professional. Hotel was quiet and I loved coming back to my room every night. Thank you for making my stay in Paris great!

The hotel and the staff of this lovely hotel in Paris was such a welcome during my first trip to Paris since 1984. The front desk staff, those cleaning the rooms, setting up for breakfast were all very responsive and attentive. My room's design (on the 5th floor) was really cool and relaxing. The breakfast offering was huge, fresh and very tasty. I had left my travel wallet in the room safe and after calling the hotel, received it back in the US within 2 weeks.
I will be back when I visit Paris again next week, and I will bring my family. The location is perfect, right on a subway line and with plenty of shopping and eating places right around the corner.
Thank you to the Hotel Le 123 Sebastopol!

Excellent Front Desk and an amazing overall experience. Free - delicious coffee and bites from 2pm to 2am!! Super location with some really nice. Eateries within walking distance. Well Done 123!! Our second stay and we will be back for sure.

Cute boutique hotel. Good breakfast.
Room was tiny. Apparently, hotel ratings di not figure room sizes.
One chair in the room was in the way as it was not designed to slide under the desk.

The mini fridge items (non alcoholic drinks) were inclusive.

My mother and I stayed here for just a few nights in June of 2022, and we were sad to leave it. The location was great. Our favorite part of this stay were the themed rooms, which gave the hotel a fun and interesting environment. In the morning there is a breakfast that is very nice and easy to grab on the go if you choose. There is an outside back patio area for eating and the weather was great for eating outside. The service was also amazing, I often had conversations with the staff at the front. When we left for the airport, they helped us arrange for a taxi.

Lovely hotel. Comfortable rooms, great breakfast. Free tea, coffee non-alcoholic drinks and pastries in the lobby. Friendly staff. Many attractions within walking distance. In short, highly recommended.

No gilding and candelabra, but with a tuned piano in the hall that anyone can play, quite a large room with a slightly alternative and artistic decor, great breakfasts, a huge bed, a bar for free (no alcohol), similarly in the main hall - sweet food and drinks until 2:00 am for free, great, intelligent and friendly service. One of the best hotels in my life and I travel a lot.

The hotel and staff are wonderful. It is a very convenient location as it is right across the street from the Metro. Rooms are always clean, staff is friendly and helpful. The breakfast is diverse and very good.

Had the most wonderful trip to Paris, and this hotel was the perfect location for getting around to see sights, shopping, and eating out. Just chose the standard double, which was beautifully decorated and clean. I loved the film theme running throughout and had private use of the cinema to watch Moulin Rouge in French! A great touch was the free minibar and pastries, and the breakfast was fantastic, smoked salmon and eggs every morning. We will definitely be coming back and would highly recommend.

I thought this hotel was fabulous, from customer service to decor. It was beautifully decorated in accordance with the movie theme. The breakfast was one of the best hotel breakfast's I have experienced, and the afternoon/evening pastries were a very nice surprise. It was so enjoyable to return after a day of sightseeing to relaxing tea and pastries, and one time we did have tea at another Astotel, which was offered to us. This hotel surpassed by expectations.

Great value, good location. Clean, comfortable and welcoming. Staff friendly and the free snacks and drinks a great touch. Breakfast is solid and the ambience was relaxing and comfortable. Would recommend for a short stay.

Great hotel and staff! We stayed for 5 nights and also opted for the breakfast at the hotel which was amazing! Friendly staff and the interior and theme of the hotel is excellent…especially for movie lovers!

A drawback was the temperature inside the rooms. Believe it or not, it can be warm in Paris during December and more so after raining. We were told that the Air conditioner is not turned on after the summer. The fan is also not on and when it is, it was only warm air. We had to request a table fan and after a few attempts, we got it for our room. First two times, someone from the hotel staff tried to convince us to keep our windows open but, we didn’t want to do that and let the air in constantly from the outside. Once this issue was resolved, the stay was quite pleasant. Thanks

we came here two days ago, our rooms were just beautiful and clean, the food was excellent. They have a movie room and the gym, you can also eat whenever you want without paying anything, it’s all included

Me and my 16 year old daughter had a fabulous time here for a long weekend getaway. The staff were AMAZING, the location was well connected to everywhere, we enjoyed eating at a great bistro next door, our room was amazing and had a small balcony, the hotel showed the World Cup in the cinema downstairs (amazing!), snacks and drinks every night was a treat, soft drinks in your room provided free of charge, and they left a birthday note for my daughter in the room as they knew it was a special occasion ahhhh- if we ever come back to Paris we will book this hotel (or one of the Astotel chain) , it is the only place we would want to stay ♥️

Good position. We book a family room, 2 rooms with a door inside, 2 bathrooms, very good for a family of 4 persons. The breakfast is good. Open frigobar in room with water , coke and juces. The beds are confortable and very quiet during the night. The price is hight, but in general good quality of services.

We were in a twin room, which was perfect for two. The room was clean and location convenient. The lobby was beautifully decorated and the people at the front desk were fluent in Englsh and eager to help.

I tried doing laundry through the hotel, but it is only available on weekdays. There is a laundromat close by that was convenient and cheap.

A wonderfull experience, cinema themed hotel. A breakfast buffet which i have never seen before. You name it...they had it. (so for all you who like their breakfast...this ones for you)
The room was lovely, beds were ok...a bit soft for me but that's each his own. The bathroom was very nice with a good size bath and shower.
For us it was no problem to get anywhere as we like to walk but if you like to go with the metro, there are some stations closeby.
Also enough Bistro's, cafe's and restaurants in the neighbourhood so you don't have to go far to get something to eat.
From 14:00 till 02:00 the snack buffet is open and you can sit and relax with the free softdrinks, thea, coffee and pattisserie. (big plus ;-)). You can also go to any Astotel in the city and show your roomkey to enjoy the Buffet in that hotel (also free)
The Staff is very nice and helpful.
Really recommend this hotel to everyone!

We have spent 4 nights with our 1,5 years old daughter in the hotel. The hotel is in beautiful shape and you can see that management is taking care of every detail.

Breakfast is rich and tasty. Free drinks in the afternoon are a great add-on. Rooms are quite and cleaning staff is very professional.

Location is very good. Close walking distance to several metro lines.

Most impressive was the engagement of the front desk during our stay. They went above and beyond to solve any problems that came up when our daughter needed support.

We would always concider this hotel when coming back to visit Paris.

Wow did this hotel get it all right! The hotel is movie themes and you walk in to a lobby styled like a movie theatre. The hotel is immaculately decorated in theme...and they have a private movie theatre you can go watch stuff in any time. And then- the room was beautifully decorated, the minibar is free, and there is a happy hour bat downstairs from 2 pm to 2 am. That is right. A 12 hour happy hour. AND, you can go to any Astotel in the city and utilize their happy hour. The bathroom was clean with luxury amenities and the bedding was comfortable. And best of all, all the hotel staff always has a smile, which is just perfect for the Christmas season!

Nice hotel situated in the 2nd arr. with a few metro stations 2 blocks from the hotel. The cinema theme was cute, but felt a bit dated. The rooms were nice and of decent size in a city like Paris, and the bathroom was roomy. I did have one issue with the shower - the shower curtain was thin and flimsy and it was hard to prevent water from splashing out onto the bathroom floor.

The mid-day snack offering was a nice touch, although I didn't get a chance to try anything. I liked that the rooms had a free selection of drinks that were refreshed daily. The hotel provided free umbrella use during the rainy month of November.

The best thing was the front desk service. Everyone who worked there was extremely pleasant and helpful!

I think this was my best visit in Europe despite staying in Paris. This chain has 16 other hotels in Paris and you can eat their snack, breakfast, etc. They upgradex our room and it was very comfy and spaceful. Even though Parisian hotel rooms are very small, this hotel surprised me. Also the minibar is getting refilled everyday with room service. Fantastic variety of breakfast and the staff is very kind and welcoming. I strongly reccomend this hotel if you are stayin in Paris

This is my favourite place to stay in Paris. I love the location, the rooms, the breakfast, the staff and I have been very happy here, staying here multiple times over the last few years. I have told many people about the hotel and others have stayed based on my recommendations. However, I am beyond disappointed with the new booking policy that is "non refundable" only available from May 2023. This means I will no longer be able to stay here as, plans change and sometimes, due to circumstances beyond our control, we need to change plans, change our bookings. Without the security of free cancellation, I will no longer be able to book here and that makes me very sad. Even if you could offer us travellers a longer free cancellation policy, ie free cancellation up to 1 week or even 2 weeks before travel, it would help immensely with having the confidence to book. For example, at the moment, I am trying to book for next May, June and July but without a free cancellation policy, I will look for hotels that still offer this policy. Please please please revert to your previous cancellation policy! I don't want to stay anywhere else!

This was my 4th or 5th stay at Le 123 Sebastopol and the highlight of this particular stay was an incredible front desk representative named Rui.

He had a great smile to match his positive "can do" attitude and went out of fire was too make sure my stay was enjoyable.

Rui is an excellent ambassador for the brand and people like him are the reason why I return.

Booked this hotel for a 5 night stay in Paris. Located in the 3rd Arrondissement directly across from the Reaumur-Sebastopol stop of the Metro. Station has access to the 3 & 4 lines, but very easy to navigate the Metro and switch trains to other lines. What I liked most about the location was it was close enough to many attractions yet far enough away from the Hustle & Bustle that you could relax and have some reprieve at the end of the day. It's like going to NYC and staying in a neighborhood like Greenwich Village vs Times Square. Plenty of cafe's and bars within walking distance. This neighborhood made you feel more immersed with the locals vs more touristy areas. We were able to walk to the Louvre from here. The Eiffel Tower requires a metro ride and you can not see from this part of the city. The hotel staff was extremely friendly and accommodating, no complaints at all. We booked a double superior room which was really a "king" bed by American standards. We were on the 6th floor in the rear of the building so had a view of a courtyard and neighboring residential apartments. Hotel has complimentary mini bar in the room with waters and soda's that were restocked every day, nice touch. The lobby had light snacks and soft drinks available all day which was also nice. We did not pay for the breakfast at the hotel as we wanted to go out and experience different cafe's each day instead. Although we did not pay for the breakfast as part of our room rate, we were offered to help ourselves if we wanted. We did one day only just to try and it was ok but nothing spectacular, what you would expect for a hotel breakfast, scrambled eggs, breakfast meats, yogurts, assortment of cheese and meats and vegetables (The American in me does not understand eating carrots and green beans for breakfast!). Wait staff will also make you coffee, cappuccino etc. Best place for breakfast within walking distance was a cafe called 46 and 3rd and would highly recommend! This location is also walking distance to night life including many local gay bars. Felt safe overall in the area walking around at night.

The breakfast and all it’s variety of foods was delicious. Thank you to the service staff who were very attentive. The afternoon availability of snacks and coffee was relied upon to give us energy to return to our tour of Paris. The room was very comfortable and quiet. Thank you to the front desk staff who were very friendly and we’re able to give us a lot of information and advice throughout our stay.

We will definitely stay here again if we are fortunate enough to return to Paris someday.

Merci Beaucoup!

Lovely stay at this hotel! Staff were very helpful at both the front desk and breakfast.

The breakfast is great. They have a large buffet that includes vegan options. The breakfast staff clarified for me which items I could eat and there were surprisingly quite a few. I also noticed they have a variety of non dairy milks and soy yoghurt.

We had a room on an upper floor with a balcony with was lovely. Great view over the square. Not too noisy.

This is the second time I have stayed at this hotel. It is really a very cozy hotel with friendly staff. I would definitely recommend this place to my friends. Clean rooms, delicious breakfast and a 24-hour snack bar with muffins, coffee and soft drinks. Thank you for a nice time.

My daughter, her best friend and I stayed at Hotel Le 123 Sebastopol- Astotel in July to celebrate her 17th Birthday. The hotel is just as it looks in the pictures. I found the staff to be very friend, accommodating and just pleasant all around. I want to specifically point out Adyl, Mourad, Xiao and Simon. They went above and beyond and made us feel welcome.

They offer complimentary afternoon snacks. My only wish was that they offered something salty, such as pretzel or popcorn in addition to all the sweets they offer.

I recently stayed at the Sebastopol and it was a lovely experience. The room was tastefully decorated, incredibly clean and comfortable. The buffet breakfast was exceptional. Fresh breads, cheese, fruits and desserts. My cappuccino was the best I have had in France so far. (It was so good I took a picture of it!) I have been in France for a week now (sadly in another part of France for the past few days so not staying at the Sabastopol currently) and I wish I had been able to stay in Paris just to stay at the hotel longer. The front desk staff and all the attendants are charming and efficient. There was some trouble with the travel agent's booking and they resolved it all swiftly and graciously. I will be back the next time I am in Paris, to be certain.

I've stayed here twice, and both times I had a great experience. Located in a really cute area, and the staff are all very friendly / helpful. Definitely recommend! The film theme is very cool and unique too!

The staff were wonderful and the location convenient to Metro, and arrondissement 3, which has great shops and restaurants. Adyl at the front desk gets a 5 star for his customer service and kindness. They have great complimentary snacks available for their guests throughout the day and evening.

Great hotel, great location (three Metro stations nearby, big grocery store just 1 minute walk) and most important of all: wonderful hospitality. They are doing everything to make your stay a pleasant one (Luana from the reception desk was extremely helpful). A private cinema, gym, sublime decoration and attention to details. We had a great time.

A lovely breakfast, we were able to find everything we need, sweat and salty, besides of the friendly and really nice staff of the hotel. A huge thanks to "Julien" who has been helpful at anytime. The room was really nice and super clean. I really recommand it.

Excellent little hotel, with a very comfortable room and bed, the room itself was decorated with fotos of French film stars.

Hotel location was on the eastern side, of the centre of Paris, and easy to walk and navigate to the centre, or by Metro.

Lovely range of food for breakfast

Had a great time at 123 Sebastopol in Paris in early September. My room on the fifth floor was clean and comfortable and QUIET. The lobby was hip and the breakfast was AMAZING. Located a nice walk from the Seine but close to Marais, etc. Great location, really. Amazing staff. In particular, I'd like to thank the night host, Luana, and the Day Managers Mourad and Lia for their excellent care. Great value. Very highly recommend!

The hotel is in an excellent location, convenient to walk to major sites but also to the metro The rooms are comfortable and clean. The staff is very pleasant and helpful. The beverages in the mini-bar and free snacks in the afternoons are a bonus. The small outdoor terrace is perfect to unwind and plan your next outing. Would highly recommend.

Very nice & comfortable hotel, good location, delicious breakfast and very clean and good rooms. The film theme is great. We were with two ladies and we really enjoyed our stay in this nice hotel, feels safe and the free minibar is very welcoming.

Hotel staff were friendly and enjoyed the tea time in the lobby. Rooms on the small side and could use some maintenance (drywall putty in bathroom was an eyesore and shelf falling down) but overall good stay in a good location!

A beautiful hotel with very helpful staff, the hotel breakfast was good, the hotel/room was clean and fresh (towels were fluffy with a beautiful soft fragrance to them, the complimentary toiletries had a beautiful perfumed fragrance to them, as-well). Shout out to Mourad the assistant manager, he was very helpful with my requests throughout the stay - also, without asking, he kindly arranged a coffee and pastries for me to takeaway for my departure flight as I didn’t have time to eat at the hotel.

For me, the location was very good as it has many good restaurants/cafes close by and is within walking distance to the tourist locations (I prefer walking but there are metro stations close by).

I would/will definitely come back and stay here again.

I really enjoyed my stay at 123 Sebastopole astotel
Everyone we’re very welcoming
Clean room
Amazing staff
Especially Philip, he made my coffe every day with a big smile , asking me how everything was , if I need anything
What a fantastic trip
I’ll be back
Thank you for the hospitality
Angela M

Honeymoon with my wife. We're in our 30s and this place was a perfect location to access all the sites of Paris. Plenty of local food options, subway and pharmacy access is across the street. The staff was very helpful with how to move around town and answering any questions. They served coffee, teas, and snacks throughout the day and breakfast was wonderful and light fares to get the morning started. The room was she conditioned, clean and very spacious! This set a very high bar for the rest of our vacation. We would love to visit this location again.

Had a quiet room on the 2nd floor. The location wasn't too great, I would beware of the nearby metro since I was pickpocketed there. The hotel itself and the staff were very accommodating and friendly.

We had a lovely stay at this hotel.
The location offers easy access to two great
metro-stations and is in a vibrant neighborhood with tons of food options close by.

The staff is helpful and incredibly polite and did what they could to accommodate us.
We loved our standard double room that was the perfect size for two adults, a spacious shower and cute french balcony.

When we return to paris we would gladly stay here again!

The hotel is beautiful and clean. The beds are very comfy, even my husband who suffers from back pain slept comfortably. The breakfast, rooms and location is the best. l could not fault them, my children had the best time in Paris better than last time when we stayed at a disneyland hotel.

Stayed here for the weekend. Beautiful rooms and common areas. Staff couldn’t do enough to help.

Special touches of cakes and coffee being available most of the day, coffee machine and mini bar in room. Even as we left they gave us some water as it was a hot day.

We will be back.

If you are looking for a great hotel in central Paris then hotel 123 Sebastopol is highly recommended.

Charming, professional and courteous staff. Lovely ambiance with a quirky design based on iconic cinematography.

Afternoon teas are a delight.

A great experience every time. Thank you hotel 123 Sebastopol.

What a gem! Superb! Excellent location, fabulous breakfast and amazing service! We celebrated our 30th Wedding Anniversary and after a fun day in Disney we returned to our room to a bottle of champagne and sweets! What a lovely surprise! We can’t thank the hotel staff enough for making our stay so memorable! We will certainly be recommending to family and friends!

Fantastic hotel. The staff were really friendly and helpful. Rooms were extremely clean with a complimentary soft mini bar, excellent. Complimentary afternoon refreshments and cakes were lovely. Great location and all round experience was faultless. Would highly recommend.

Very good hotel in excellent location. Staff were very friendly, polite and helpful.
We had adjoining rooms for ourselves and our two children which was perfect for our needs.
Free soft drinks in mini bar and free drinks and snacks in the lobby was a very nice touch.
Highly recommended.

We had 10 extraordinary days at this wonderful hotel. Excellent location, wonderful breakfast, snacks, and super helpful staff. The shower, air con and beds were excellent! Simon was so helpful and kind. There are a ton of great cafes and restaurants within minutes of the hotel, and the metro is super convenient. Don’t hesitate to book here! Loved every minute.

We loved our stay at 123 Sebastopol in Paris! The workers were incredibly helpful and welcoming. We loved that there was an afternoon snack and that we could leverage the other area hotel facilities, as well. The rooms here were great, as were the common areas and the outdoor patio. We appreciated the location of the hotel, as well-close to everything with an authentic French feel, without the tourism chaos. Everything exceeded our expectations and when we come back for another visit, we’ll likely book here again. Thank you for making our stay so enjoyable!

Fantastic hotel! Each member of the staff was incredibly friendly and helpful, no exception. Good variation in breakfast, and tasty. Nicely decorated and clean rooms. Bed was comfortable, though the pillow could be better. I slept well though. Bathroom was fine. Sometimes the temperature in the shower was a bit shaky, but it didn't bother me too much. Location was perfect. Centrally located and near a metro station with a direct connection (four stops only) to Gard du Nord.
Warmly recommended!

We stayed at this hotel as a family of 4 for 9 nights and we absolutely enjoyed our stay. The family room we stayed in was very spacious and private, so we could rest really well. We also stayed in the double room and twin room for the last couple of nights and those rooms were very nice too. All of the staff were very helpful and friendly, and they went out of their way to help us. Their breakfast was fabulous with a lot of hot bar items (not just eggs and meats) every morning (i.e., total opposite of typical free breakfast in American chain hotels). The free drink minibar (non-alcohol) in each room was a nice touch. Also, they offer all day snacks in the lobby so that you can rest and munch on some sweets after a long day of sightseeing around. Because of this, we hardly needed to buy any water on our own. There were some Metro stations very close by (Réaumur – Sébastopol and Strasbourg-Saint-Denis) too, so it was very easy to get around in Paris. We Highly recommend this hotel!
